Definition: a Protestant movement in the 16th century that believed in the primacy of the Bible, baptised only believers, not infants, and believed in complete separation of church and state
Synonyms: noun, person, anabaptist, Protestantism, a, Protestant, movement, in, the, th, century, that, believed, primacy, of, Bible, baptised, only, believers, not, infants, and, complete, separation, church, state
Category: noun.cognition
